&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Strategy &amp; Business Development Directorate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kings Court 2, Worcester&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Programmes &amp; Business Support Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust’s Business Development, Planning and Programmes Team are looking for a motivated, positive and flexible individual to provide high quality management support in a friendly and supportive environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based at the Trust’s new headquarters on the outskirts of Worcester (but working from home for a minimum of three days a week during the current Covid-19 pandemic),  you will join a small team that is dedicated to providing high quality support to clinical, operational and corporate colleagues, setting priorities, pursuing opportunities and co-ordinating a wide range of projects to help the Trust deliver its goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the Team’s Programmes and Business Support Manager, you will support the Head of Business Development, Planning and Programmes in delivering the team’s three primary functions – business development, business planning and programme management, as well as have the opportunity to develop your skills and profile by contributing to a number of exciting projects, and working closely with a wide range of Trust and partner organisation colleagues.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate recent and relevant experience working within a health and care environment, as well as excellent communication and presentational skills (both written and verbal), experience using project management tools and techniques, a  project management qualification or evidence of successfully completing a project management related course, and experience of managing or supervising staff.  Business development and/or business planning experience would also be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel this is the job for you and would like to discuss further, please contact Mark Smedley, Head of Business Development, Planning and Programmes on 07917 146232 or mark.smedley@nhs.net.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
